      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<h2 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-Introduction\">Introduction</h2><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"1280\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/RenderMan_Katana_PresetBrowser.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542494&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=557\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/546179237/RenderMan_Katana_PresetBrowser.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542494&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"557\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"546179264\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Katana_PresetBrowser.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"546179237\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"bebbfcc0-a185-4377-9993-0edf7111a0cf\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/RenderMan_Katana_PresetBrowser.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542494&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=557 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/RenderMan_Katana_PresetBrowser.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542494&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=557 1x\"></span><ul><li><p>You can open the Preset Browser using the menu arrow button and looking under RenderMan.</p></li><li><p>Presets include categories for light rigs, environment lights, and materials.</p></li><li><p>You can search for assets by name, usage category, or metadata.</p></li></ul><h2 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-SavingandUsing\">Saving and Using</h2><ul><li><p>Saving/Exporting a material is easy!</p><ul><li><p>You must select the BxDF <em>network material</em> from the <em>Scene Graph</em> (the export will recognize connected nodes) Note: the factory library cannot be modified, you can make a copy or create a new library</p></li></ul></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"500\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserMakeLibrary.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542494&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=500&amp;height=277\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserMakeLibrary.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542494&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"279\" data-width=\"502\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"546179258\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfk_presetBrowserMakeLibrary.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"546179237\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"4cbd3f3a-e7dc-48c4-bf5a-0dbad2a8c121\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserMakeLibrary.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542494&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=502&amp;height=279 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserMakeLibrary.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542494&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=500&amp;height=277 1x\"></span><ul><li><p>Choose the category you want from the Preset Browser (Material, Light, etc)</p></li><li><p>Choose the Save icon (the shiny material ball+ icon underneath the preview image)</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"500\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSelectMat.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=452&amp;height=432\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSelectMat.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"432\" data-width=\"452\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"546179252\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfk_presetBrowserSelectMat.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"546179237\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"39d4e164-3a4f-4cb6-beea-8281c83794cb\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSelectMat.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=452&amp;height=432 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSelectMat.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=452&amp;height=432 1x\"></span><ul><li><p>Give it a useful name and any desired metadata for your pipeline</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"500\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSaveMat.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=500&amp;height=277\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSaveMat.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"279\" data-width=\"502\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"546179255\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfk_presetBrowserSaveMat.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"546179237\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"8ccaac8e-593b-458d-8d30-2e606bddd6f9\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSaveMat.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=502&amp;height=279 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSaveMat.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=500&amp;height=277 1x\"></span><ul><li><p>RenderMan will generate a preview swatch render, this will auto-populate in the Preset Browser</p></li><li><p>Saving light rigs is the same except you use the little lightbulb icon with the + symbol next to the material save preset icon. You can export a Gaffer node or individual lights.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"500\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSelectLght.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=452&amp;height=432\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSelectLght.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"432\" data-width=\"452\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"546179249\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfk_presetBrowserSelectLght.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"546179237\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"2588bb4f-a838-428f-9afc-7b38922670be\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSelectLght.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=452&amp;height=432 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/546179237/rfk_presetBrowserSelectLght.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754531542270&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=452&amp;height=432 1x\"></span><ul><li><p>Importing/Using a saved asset</p><ul><li><p>Simply right-click and choose &quot;Import and Assign&quot; to a selected object</p></li><li><p>Make any adjustments for your object as needed!</p></li></ul></li></ul><p /><h2 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-EnvironmentMaps\">Environment Maps</h2><ul><li><p>You can save an Environment Map using the image icon+ underneath the large preview swatch in the Preset Browser</p><ul><li><p>Select the Environment category in the Preset Browser</p></li><li><p>Choose the desired OpenEXR or .HDR file from the file browser window</p></li><li><p>You can add/change metadata in the dialog or change the name.</p></li><li><p>Then we convert the image to a compatible .tex format. This may take time depending on the original image size.</p></li><li><p>A preview render is then performed and automatically populated in the browser category.</p></li></ul></li><li><p>Using a saved map is easy.</p><ul><li><p>Right-click the asset and import.</p></li><li><p>Changing the map is as easy as double-clicking another environment map asset!</p></li></ul></li></ul><p style=\"text-align: center;\"></p><h2 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-AssetDependencies\">Asset Dependencies</h2><p>When an asset is saved to disk, all its dependencies are saved to disk too. </p><p>These include :</p><ul><li><p><strong>Textures</strong> : stored in tex format, UDIM is supported.</p></li><li><p><strong>HDRI environment maps</strong> : stored in tex format. We use a specific combination of flags to compress the texture as efficiently as possible.</p></li><li><p><strong>OSL shaders</strong> : stored in oso format to protect your IP, but you can manually add the osl file in the asset directory if you want to share the source code.</p></li></ul><p>These dependencies can increase the size of a preset on disk and you should bear that in mind if you want to distribute them over the internet.</p><p /><h2 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-Cross-ApplicationMaterials\">Cross-Application Materials</h2><p>RenderManAssets have been designed to be easily transferable from one application (like Katana) to another (Maya, Houdini, Blender, etc) and vice-versa.</p><h3 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-CompatibilityIssues\">Compatibility Issues</h3><p>Still, it is possible to run into compatibility issues if your material contains non-native RenderMan nodes. For example, RenderMan for Maya automatically converts a number of native Maya nodes which won't be available in Katana, e.g. the file node or Maya's Cloud pattern. To mitigate these problems, each RenderManAsset maintains a list of used nodes and use it to evaluate the preset's compatibility with the current host application and display a warning if it is not compatible.</p><p>The system will check :</p><ul><li><p>if the asset contains host-specific nodes</p></li><li><p>if the asset's renderer version is superior or equal to the current version</p></li><li><p>if the asset contains host-specific nodes, make sure the current host version is superior or equal to the asset's host version.</p></li></ul><h3 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-BestPractice\">Best Practice</h3><p>If you want to ensure cross-application compatibility, avoid non-Pixar BxDFs and Patterns.</p><p /><h2 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-LibraryConfiguration\">Library Configuration</h2><p>RenderMan ships with a standard library that can be found in : <code>$RMANTREE/lib/RenderManAssetLibrary</code></p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"7afa94af-9518-4e6f-a7ef-4e55ac65525a\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>We recommend that you copy the standard library to a location of your choice and leave the default library untouched as a backup. The new copy should be readable and writable. The asset browser will not allow you to create new assets if it points to a non-writable location.</p></div></div><h3 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-Environmentvariable\">Environment variable</h3><p>The location of the asset library can be set through the <code>RMAN_ASSET_LIBRARY</code> environment variable.</p><p>It can be set using different methods :</p><h5 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-Linux/OSX\"><strong>Linux / OS X</strong></h5><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"a0291fe1-37bd-4540-a5ed-5bedde26ef46\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">RMAN_ASSET_LIBRARY = $RMANTREE/lib/RenderManAssetLibrary</pre>\n</div></div><h5 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-Windows\"><strong>Windows</strong></h5><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"8189c5cd-f7f4-499e-8244-43c717523085\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">RMAN_ASSET_LIBRARY = %RMANTREE%/lib/RenderManAssetLibrary</pre>\n</div></div><h4 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-Systemcommands\">System commands</h4><h5 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-Linux\">Linux</h5><p>On all Posix platforms (Linux &amp; OSX), you can either define the environment variable in the shell you will launch Katana from or append it to your shell configuration file (<code>.cshrc</code> for csh/tcsh, <code>.profile</code> or <code>.bashrc</code> for bash).</p><h5 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-csh/tcsh\"><strong>csh / tcsh</strong></h5><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"9a268c75-8dc4-457a-8775-e9f4cfa95fc1\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">setenv RMAN_ASSET_LIBRARY $RMANTREE/lib/RenderManAssetLibrary</pre>\n</div></div><h5 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-bash\"><strong>bash</strong></h5><div class=\"code panel pdl conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"5bd4f0bc-17dc-40a3-b662-e96731ccf609\" data-macro-name=\"code\" style=\"border-width: 1px;\"><div class=\"codeContent panelContent pdl\">\n<pre class=\"syntaxhighlighter-pre\" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=\"brush: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence\" data-theme=\"Confluence\">export RMAN_ASSET_LIBRARY=$RMANTREE/lib/RenderManAssetLibrary</pre>\n</div></div><h5 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-OSX\">OSX</h5><ul><li><p>If you are running Katana from the shell, you can setup your environment variables like Linux.</p></li></ul><h5 id=\"PresetBrowserinKatana-Windows.1\">Windows</h5><ul><li><p>Right-click My Computer and choose Properties (or double-click System in the control panel), then click the Advanced tab, and click Environment Variables.</p></li></ul>"
    }
  },
